A lot of libraries are like this because Acid were never very respectful of the OS and a lot of 
cool things we have now did not exist back then (e.g. AHI).

One sure-fire way of escaping the problems is to use OS calls directly (well, and hope that the 
OS library interface for that library is not broken :)

> The are some libs doing very bad stuff and I have to find out
> which.

From what I remember the problems are mainly caused by:
- Acid libraries which work with the OS
- Some RWE libraries
- Elmore libraries (a lot)

> BTW: The StringGadget command of the gadgetslib
> (NOT Davids Gadtools lib) causes a lot of
> enforcer hits and crashes Amithlon sooner or later.
> Is this known and is there an update or do I have to
> rewrite my proggy with Davids GT lib ?

Use gadtools if possible. The commands are not too much different and you will gain more 
features (I do not think you lose any). The gadgetslib is a GUI library for OS 1.3(!). Even 
gadtools nowadays is "outdated" (since they are trying to make Reaction the standard GUI).

