@NODE "mail_25" " Re: Modifying Screen Tags "
From: amorel <amorel@...>
Date: 01-10-03 06:47:15
Subject: @{b}Re: Modifying Screen Tags@{ub}

On Wed, Jan 08, 2003 at 09:43:34PM +0000, Steve Hargreaves wrote:
> Is there a way to modify the tags of a screen that's already open. I'm trying to
> force a particular private screen to be public, and whilst I can modify the
> screens flags to include the public flag, I also need to modify (or set)
> #PubName, #PubSig and #PubTask, but can't find a way to do it :o/

Use PubScreenStatus_(*screen,flag)
And flag is either #PSNF_PRIVATE to make it private or 0 to make it public. You don`t 
need to change #PubName, #PubSig and #PubTask, you should set those when you open the 
screen and they will be used when you make a screen public. There is no way afaik to 
set these later.

Regards 

---------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

